BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by ITAR-TASS correspondent Yefim Shvartsman] </F>
  [Text] Odessa 12 April, TASS -- No more incidents have been 
reported from the 318th Division of the Black Sea Fleet to be 
made the 1st Brigade of the Ukrainian Navy under an order of 
Ukrainian Defence Minister General of the Army Vitaliy Radetskyy. 
  Commander of the Odessa Military District Colonel-General 
Vladimir Shkidchenko visited the Division's First Brigade on 
Tuesday. 
  Four officers and 12 warrant officers of the 318th Black Sea 
Fleet division said they want to serve in the Ukrainian Navy, 
sources told ITAR-TASS. All in all, some 200 Division officers 
shall decide on their further service. The officers that make a 
negative decision will be offered a transfer to other Russian 
fleets. 
  When asked whether the officers' rights will be protected 
and 
their Odessa apartments will be left at their disposal, 
Shkidchenko said "none is planning deportation of the families, 
they will stay where they are if they want to". 
  The new commander -- Captain 2nd Class Vladimir Marchenko -- 
was introduced to the Brigade personnel. 

